Dr. Marta S. Contigiani
Head, Dr. J. M. Vanella Virology Institute - FCM - UNC
Arbovirus Laboratory
Enfermera Gordillo Gomez s/n
Ciudad Universitaria, Cordoba, Argentina
<contigia@cmefcm.uncor.edu>
[ProMED is grateful to Dr. Marta S. Contigiani for this special report on the
detailed investigation of the outbreak of SLEV infections and deaths in
Cordoba, including serologic and molecular confirmation. [In addition], 2
strains of SLEV were successfully isolated and partially sequenced from
captured Culex mosquitoes from 3 infected pools. - Mod.RY]
[SLE is endemic in wild birds throughout South America, and is transmitted to
humans when a mosquito that has previously fed on an infected bird feeds again
on a human. For a diagram of the transmission cycle see:
<http://www.lawestvector.org/images/Arbocycl.GIF>
Given that West Nile virus is on its way south in migrating birds, it is
important to use lab diagnostic tests such as PCR that clearly distinguish
these 2 diseases. - Mod.JW]
